name: Aerobic
effect: Aerobic causes the Temtem to get SPDEF and SPD whenever they use a Wind Technique.

name: Air Specialist
effect: Air Specialist increases the damage of the user's Wind Techniques by an additional 15%.

name: Amphibian
description: Whenever a Temtem with Amphibian is attacked by a Water Technique, it gets SPD and ATK .

name: Anaerobic
description: Whenever a Temtem with Anaerobic uses a Toxic Technique, it gets SPDEF and SPATK .

name: Apothecary
description: Whenever a Temtem with Apothecary attacks with a Special Technique, if the target is an enemy, it inflicts the Poisoned Condition for 1 turn, or if the target is an ally or itself, it inflicts the Regenerated Condition for 1 turn.

name: Attack T
effect: Attack<T> changes the user's secondary Type to match the Technique they are about to use. If the move the Temtem is about to use is the same type as that Temtem's primary type, then the Temtem becomes a single-type Temtem of that type. For example, Oree becomes a Digital/Electric Temtem when using Tesla Prison, and becomes pure Digital when using Turbo Attack.

name: Autotomy
effect: Autotomy causes the user to get the Evading Condition for 2 turns upon its first entry onto the battlefield.

name: Avenger
description: A Temtem with Avenger gets SPATK and SPD whenever its ally is knocked out.

name: Benefactor
description: Whenever the ally of the Temtem with Benefactor takes damage from a technique (no matter the target), they are healed by 10% of their max HP. This effect has no minimum value, meaning it can heal the ally for more HP than they lost due to getting attacked. It will only trigger if they take damage from the technique.

name: Body Stretch
description: Whenever a Temtem with Body Stretch rests, it gains the Regenerated Condition for 2 turns.

name: Book Lungs
description: Whenever a Temtem with Book Lungs takes damage from a Water technique, the damage is reduced by 50%.

name: Botanist
description: Botanist increases the damage of the user's Nature Techniques by an additional 15%.

name: Botanophobia
description: Whenever a Temtem with Botanophobia is attacked by a Nature Technique, the damage is increased by 50%.

name: Brawny
description: A Temtem with Brawny has all damage done by Physical Techniques boosted by an additional 20%.

name: Bully
description: If the number of allies conscious is greater than the number of enemies conscious, including Temtem not on the battlefield for both totals, then Temtem with Bully deal an additional 30% more damage.

name: Burglar
description: When a Temtem with Burglar attacks another Temtem that has the Asleep Condition or the Exhausted Condition, the defender's gear will be disabled for the remainder of the combat.

name: Caffeinated
description: Temtem with Caffeinated will never receive the Asleep Condition.

name: Callosity
description: Whenever a Temtem with Callosity gets attacked by a Physical Technique, it then gets DEF . It cannot be triggered more than once per turn.

name: Camaraderie
description: When a Temtem with Camaraderie is attacked, if its ally is part of its evolutionary line, then it takes 50% less damage.

name: Channeler
description: Special Techniques used by a Temtem with Channeler do 25% more damage.

name: Cobweb
description: Whenever a Temtem with Cobweb causes another Temtem to get the Poisoned Condition, or when it attacks a target that already has the Poisoned Condition, it also causes it to get the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.

name: Cold-Blooded
effect: Cold-Blooded causes the Temtem to gain the Regenerated Condition for 2 turns whenever its inflicted with the Cold Condition and prevents the Cold Condition from applying.

name: Cold-Natured
description: Whenever a Temtem with Cold-Natured would get the Cold Condition, they instead get the Frozen Condition for the same amount of turns.

name: Comebacker
effect: When an attacker targets a Temtem with Comebacker, the attacker takes 35% increased damage for the rest of the turn.

name: Common Factor
effect: When entering the battlefield, rivals and the ally get nullified for 2 turns.

name: Confined
description: When a Temtem with Confined uses a technique that causes it to give itself the Trapped Condition, it also gets DEF and SPDEF .

name: Coward's Rest
description: Whenever a Temtem with Coward's Rest rests, it gains the Evading Condition for 2 turns.

name: Deceit Aura
description: For the first four turns in which a Temtem with Deceit Aura is present on the battlefield, the individual Temtem turn order is reversed. This reversal applies to the order in which techniques are used and the order in which Temtem are swapped. Temtem swapping and item usage still occur prior to techniques.

name: Defuser
description: When a Temtem with Defuser attacks another Temtem with a physical technique, the target of the attack will recieve the Seized Condition for 3 turns.

name: Demoralize
description: When a Temtem with Demoralize enters the battlefield, both enemies immediately get SPD , even if they are then immediately after swapped out.

name: Determined
description: Temtem with Determined can never have its stats decreased by any amount of stages.

name: Dreaded Alarm
description: Whenever the enemy of a Temtem with Dreaded Alarm rests, they lose 25% of their maximum HP.

name: Earthbound
description: Earthbound gives the user DEF whenever they use an Earth technique.

name: Effective Denial
effect: Currently, Effective Denial is unobtainable, so it's unknown what its full effect is.

name: Efficient
description: When a Temtem with Efficient uses an offensive technique, the technique costs 30% less stamina.

name: Electric Custodian
effect: Electric Techniques targeting an ally will target this Temtem instead.

name: Electric Synthesize
description: When a Temtem with Electric Synthesize is attacked with a damaging Electric Technique, it restores their HP equal to the amount of damage they would have received.

name: Energy Reserves
description: As soon as a Temtem with Energy Reserves has 40% or less of its maximum HP, the Temtem gets the Vigorized Condition for 2 turns and ATK . This will only happen once per battle.

name: Escapist
description: While a Temtem with Escapist is on the battlefield, neither it nor its ally can get the Trapped Condition. Also, when it enters the battlefield, its ally loses the Trapped Condition if it has it.

name: Fainted Curse
description: When a Temtem with Fainted Curse is knocked-out by a damage dealing Technique, the attacker loses 30% of their max HP.

name: Fast Charge
description: When a Digital Temtem enters the battlefield, it gets SPD if its ally has Fast Charge.

name: Fever Rush
description: Whenever a Temtem with Fever Rush receives any status condition, it also gets ATK .

name: Flawed Crystal
description: Whenever a Temtem with Flawed Crystal takes damage from a technique that is either Mental, Toxic, or Electric, it takes 50% increased damage.

name: Friendship
description: Whenever the ally of a Temtem with Friendship uses an offensive technique that would target it, the technique instead has no effects on that Temtem. If the technique also targeted enemies, they will still be affected.

name: Frightening
effect: Gear equipped on both opponent and allied Temtem will not have any effect on the holders or other Temtem for the first 2 turns a Temtem with Frightening is present on the battlefield.

name: Furor
description: When the HP of a Temtem with Furor is below 33% of its maximum, the techniques it uses do 33% more damage.

name: Going Away Gift
effect: When knocked-out, adds the Temtem positive stat state changes to the ally.

name: Good Friend
effect: Temtem

name: Gotta Go Fast
effect: Changes the Temtem's very low, low and normal priority techniques to high priority.

name: Guardian
description: The ally of a Temtem with Guardian cannot get the Cold Condition, Burned Condition, Poisoned Condition, or Doomed Condition, nor can it receive any negative stage changes to its stats.

name: Half Full
effect: Temtem

name: Heat Discharge
description: When a Temtem knocks out another Temtem with Heat Discharge, it gets the Burned Condition for 3 turns.

name: Heater
effect: Temtem

name: Hover
description: Temtem with Hover take 50% less damage from Earth techniques.

name: Hurry-wart
description: When a Temtem with Hurry-wart enters the battlefield, all its techniques with a Hold lose 1 Hold.

name: Hydrologist
description: Hydrologist increases the damage of the user's Water Techniques by an additional 15%.

name: Immunity
effect: Immunity makes the Temtem take no damage from incoming Toxic Techniques and can't be inflicted with the Poisoned Condition.

name: Individualist
description: Temtem with Individualist cannot affect their ally with offensive techniques. If the technique also targets enemies, they will still be affected.

name: Inductor
description: Any time an Electric type Technique is used, all Temtem with Inductor on the field will restore 8% of their maximum HP.

name: Infectious
effect: Invalidates the regenerating effects on rivals.

name: Intimidator
effect: The Traits of both opponent and allied Temtem will not have any effect on themselves or other Temtem for the first 2 turns a Temtem with Intimidator is present on the battlefield.

name: Iridescence
description: The damage multipliers based on technique types are reversed. (Very) effective matchups become (very) ineffective and vice versa.

name: Kinetic Transfer
effect: Currently, Kinetic Transfer is unobtainable, so it's unknown what its full effect is.

name: Landing Transmog
effect: Temtem

name: Last Rush
description: If the number of allies conscious is less than the number of enemies conscious, including Temtem not on the battlefield for both totals, Temtem with Last Rush deal 30% more damage.

name: Loneliness
effect: Loneliness makes the Temtem unable to use Synergies with its ally and the ally can't use synergies with it.

name: Marathonist
description: Marathonist causes the user to get SPD when attacking, but the stamina cost of the attack is reduced by 50%.

name: Mental Alliance
description: Temtem with Mental Alliance get a 15% increase to their SPATK if their ally is Mental.

name: Mirroring
description: Whenever a Temtem with Mirroring receives damage from a Special technique, the attacker receives 40% of the damage as well if the Temtem wasn't knocked out.

name: Mithridatism
description: Temtem with Mithridatism never receive the Poisoned Condition.

name: Motivator
description: At the start of the turn, if a Temtem with Motivator is on the battlefield, all its allies, including those not on the battlefield, restore 10% of their maximum STA.

name: Mucous
description: Temtem with Mucous never receive the Cold Condition nor the Burned Condition. Additionally, they take 30% less damage from Electric or Toxic type Techniques.

name: Neurotoxins
effect: When inflicting a Temtem with the Poisoned Condition, it will instead inflict that Temtem with the Doomed Condition for 4 turns without the initial Poison.

name: Neutrality
description: Temtem with Neutrality never receive any negative status conditions.

name: Parrier
description: Whenever a Temtem with Parrier is attacked by a Physical Technique, it takes 30% less damage.

name: Patient
description: Whenever a Temtem with Patient uses a technique with a Hold, it restores 10% of its maximum STA.

name: Physmaster
effect: Temtem

name: Pigment Inverter
effect: When attacking, type resistances for the target TemTem are reversed.

name: Plethoric
description: If a Temtem with Plethoric's HP is at 70% or higher its SPD is increased by 30%.

name: Power Nap
description: At the start of the turn, if a Temtem with Power Nap has the Asleep Condition, it restores 15% of its maximum HP.

name: Prideful
description: When a Temtem with Prideful attacks another Temtem and knocks it out, it gets ATK , SPATK , and SPD .

name: Protector
description: When a Temtem with Protector enters the battlefield, it loses 10% of its maximum HP and gets Trapped Condition for 2 turns, and its ally gets DEF and SPDEF , even if the ally is immediately then swapped out.

name: Provident
description: Whenever a Temtem with Provident is attacked by a technique that is either , , or , it gets SPDEF .

name: Punching Bag
description: If a Temtem with Punching Bag is attacked by a Technique, it takes 30% less damage.

name: Puppet Master
description: If a Temtem with Puppet Master becomes the target of a single-target attack while its HP is below 40%, its ally becomes the target instead.

name: Pyromaniac
description: Pyromaniac increases the damage of the user's Fire Techniques by an additional 15%.

name: Receptive
description: Temtem with Receptive have the duration of the Vigorized Condition, the Immune Condition, the Regenerated Condition, the Evading Condition, and the Alerted Condition increased by 1 turn.

name: Rejuvenate
description: After attacking with a Special Technique, if the attacking Temtem has Rejuvenate, it restores 7% of its maximum HP.

name: Relaxed
effect: Restores 15% of max HP after not receiving any rival attacks during the turn.

name: Resilient
description: If a Temtem with Resilient is to knock itself out due to overexertion, it will instead survive with 1 HP and get SPD . Resilient can only trigger once per battle.

name: Resistant
description: Temtem with Resistant have the duration of the Cold Condition, the Asleep Condition, the Trapped Condition, the Seized Condition, the Poisoned Condition, the Burned Condition, and the Exhausted Condition decreased by 1 turn.

name: Rested
description: Temtem with Rested gets an increase of 30% to its ATK and SPATK for the first 2 turns it is present on the battlefield.

name: Royal Jelly
effect: At the start of the turn the user and its ally restore 3% of their max HP.

name: Scavenger
description: Whenever another Temtem, ally or enemy, is knocked out, the Temtem with Scavenger restores 20% of their maximum HP.

name: Self-Esteem
description: When a Temtem with Self-Esteem attacks and knocks out a Temtem and is affected by the Cold Condition, the Trapped Condition, the Seized Condition, the Poisoned Condition, the Burned Condition, the Doomed Condition, the Isolated Condition, or the Exhausted Condition, the condition is removed.

name: Sensei
description: Whenever a Temtem with Sensei attacks with a Physical Technique, SPATK is used instead of ATK. Similarly, if it is a Special Technique, it uses ATK instead of SPATK.

name: Sentinel
description: While a Temtem with Sentinel is on the battlefield, neither it nor the ally can get the Asleep Condition. Also, when it enters the battlefield, if the ally has the Asleep Condition, it loses it.

name: Seppuku
effect: When attacking and knocked-out due to overexertion, the target gets doomed for 2 turns.

name: Settling
description: Each turn a Temtem with Settling is on the battlefield, its ATK increases by 8%. However, if it leaves the battlefield, this cumulative bonus is reset.

name: Shared Pain
description: If a Temtem with Shared Pain is attacked twice in the same turn, the second attack gets redirected to the ally.

name: Skull Helmet
description: Temtem with Skull Helmet take 25% less damage from techniques that are either Mental or Melee.

name: Snowstorm
description: When entering the battlefield for the first time, rivals and the ally get cold for 3 turns if they aren't cold already.
effect: When a Temtem with Snowstorm enters the battlefield, their ally and both rivals each get the Cold Condition for 3 turns if they do not already have the condition.

name: Soft Touch
description: When a Temtem with Soft Touch attacks a target afflicted with the Asleep Condition with a damage dealing technique, the condition will not be removed, and the damage will be increased by 20%.

name: Source Replicator
effect: Temtem

name: Specmaster
effect: Temtem

name: Splitter
effect: When attacked with a physical or special technique, prevents all negative status conditions.

name: Spoilsport
description: Whenever a Temtem with Spoilsport uses a Technique that can hit multiple targets, it does 25% more damage.

name: Spreader
description: Whenever a Temtem with Spreader attacks with a Special Technique, if there are multiple enemy Temtem on the battlefield, the attack affects the entire target team instead but only deals ~66% damage.

name: Stabmaster
description: Damage done with matching type techniques is increased by 40%.
effect: When a Temtem with Stabmaster uses a technique that shares a type with it, it deals 40% extra damage in addition to the STAB bonus.

name: Striking Transmog
effect: Temtem

name: Strong Liver
description: When a Temtem with Strong Liver is attacked with a damaging Technique, it restores their HP equal to the amount of damage they would have recieved.

name: Synergy Master
description: Whenever a Temtem with Synergy Master or its ally uses a Synergy Technique, it does 25% more damage.

name: Synertyper
effect: Damage done with techniques is increased by 30% if both allies share a type.

name: Tactical Strike
description: Whenever a Temtem with Tactical Strike attacks with a technique with a hold of 1 or more, it deals 15% more damage.

name: Tardy Rush
description: After a Temtem with Tardy Rush has been on the battlefield for 3 turns in a row, its SPD increases by 100% and its ATK by 10% until it leaves the battlefield. If it is swapped in, the turn it enters the battlefield counts as turn 1.

name: Team Elusive
description: When a Temtem, whether enemy or ally, uses a multi-target technique that would hit a Temtem with Team Elusive, instead, it isn't affected. If Puppet Master would cause a Temtem with Team Elusive to be the target of an attack, it will. Puppet Master does not trigger Team Elusive.

name: Thick Skin
description: Temtem with Thick Skin take 50% less damage from  Wind Techniques.

name: Tireless
description: When a Temtem with Tireless overexerts, it doesn't lose its next turn, and it gets ATK . It will still be able to use a Technique.

name: Toxic Affinity
description: Toxic Affinity multiplies the base damage of the user's Toxic Techniques by x1.5, as if the user had STAB (Same-Type Attack Bonus). This stacks with actual STAB if the user is also a Toxic Temtem, resulting in a total multiple of x2.25 (1.5 x 1.5).

name: Toxic Farewell
description: When a Temtem knocks out a target with Toxic Farewell, it loses 10% of its maximum HP and gets the Poisoned Condition for 3 turns.

name: Toxic Skin
description: When a Temtem uses a Physical Technique on a target with Toxic Skin, the attacker gets the Poisoned Condition for 2 turns.

name: Trance
description: If a Temtem with Trance is the target of a technique, and afterwards its HP is 30% or less of its maximum, it gets the Asleep Condition for 2 turns and the Regenerated Condition for 4 turns, and also gets SPATK and SPDEF . This is regardless of if the technique did damage, but Trance only can ever trigger once per battle.

name: Trauma
description: When a Temtem with Trauma takes damage from a Physical Technique, it gets DEF . When it is takes damage from a Special Technique, it gets SPDEF .

name: Tri-Apothecary
description: Whenever a Temtem with Tri-Apothecary attacks using a Special Technique, if the target is an enemy, it inflicts the Poisoned Condition for 3 turns, or if the target is an ally or itself, it inflicts the Regenerated Condition for 3 turns.

name: Unnoticed
description: When a Temtem with Unnoticed lasts a whole turn without being targeted by any rival attacks, it gets SPD .

name: Vigorous
description: When Temtem with Vigorous use a technique that causes it to overexert, the damage is increased 50%.

name: Voltaic Charge
description: When a Temtem with Voltaic Charge is attacked with a single-target technique, it will inflict 10% damage to the attacker.

name: Voodoo
effect: When attacking an ally, the damage is replicated to each rival.

name: Warm-Blooded
description: Temtem with Warm-Blooded will never receive the Cold Condition.

name: Water Affinity
description: Water Affinity multiplies the base damage of the user's Water techniques by x1.5, as if the user had STAB (Same-Type Attack Bonus). This stacks with actual STAB if the user is also a Water type, resulting in a total multiple of x2.25 (1.5 x 1.5).

name: Water Custodian
description: While a Temtem with Water Custodian is on the battlefield, any Water techniques that target the ally will target this Temtem instead.

name: Water Synthesizer
description: When a Temtem with Water Synthesizer is attacked with a damaging Water Technique, it restores their HP equal to the amount of damage they would have received.

name: Wax Bath
effect: When the ally of the user rests, they get SPDEF .

name: Withdrawal
description: Whenever a Temtem with Withdrawal rests for their turn, they recover 20% of their maximum HP and if they had the Asleep Condition or the Poisoned Condition, they lose it.

name: Wrecked Farewell
description: Whenever a Temtem with Wrecked Farewell is knocked out by itself, such as by self-damaging techniques or by overexerting, all enemy Temtem lose 25% of their maximum HP.

name: Zen
description: Whenever a Temtem with Zen gets the Asleep Condition, it also gets DEF and SPDEF .
